title: What channel is Texas Rangers-Toronto Blue Jays on? TV, live stream for ALDS Game 1
text:
The Toronto Blue Jays and Texas Rangers begin their American League Division Series tonight at the Rogers Centre.
David Price will take the mound for the Blue Jays against Texas' Yovani Gallardo.
The game starts at 3:30 p.m. and will be televised by Fox Sports 1.
Here's how to catch Fox Sports 1 in Central New York:
Time Warner: Channel 400 (SD & HD) Verizon Fios: Channel 583 (HD) and 83 (SD) DirectTV: Channel 219 (SD & HD) Dish Network: Channel 150 (SD &HD) New Visions: Channel 768 (HD) and 83 (SD) You can also watch online or through tablets and mobile devices using FOX Sports GO .
